   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, John Shrady in Clinton, Tenn. to Jeannie Lockhart</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>In this letter, dated March 27, 1864 from Clinton, Tenn., to "My Own Darling," John Shrady, a regimental surgeon, expresses regret that he cannot be with her during Easter and informs her of his plans to request a period of leave. Additionally, he discusses the Confederate capture of the pay rolls and its subsequent impact on his own pay and provides an update concerning his $125.00 claim for a lost horse and "equipments."</abstract>
